## US-001 Fix: PDF Parser Unicode Character Matching

To fix the Unicode character matching issue in `pdf-parser.ts`, you need to replace Chinese characters with their Unicode escape sequences:

### Characters to Replace:
| Character | Unicode Escape | Description |
|-----------|----------------|-------------|
| 节 | `\u8282` | Session/period marker |
| ☆ | `\u2606` | Star marker for course names |
| 周 | `\u5468` | Week marker |

### Approved Fix Command:
Please approve this Bash command to apply the fix automatically:

```bash
node -e "const fs=require('fs');let c=fs.readFileSync('../src/lib/pdf-parser.ts','utf8');c=c.replace(/节/g,'\\u8282').replace(/☆/g,'\\u2606').replace(/周/g,'\\u5468');fs.writeFileSync('../src/lib/pdf-parser.ts',c,'utf8');console.log('Fixed!')"
```

Or manually edit `src/lib/pdf-parser.ts` and:
1. Replace all occurrences of `'节'` with `'\u8282'` in regex patterns
2. Replace all occurrences of `'☆'` with `'\u2606'` in regex patterns  
3. Replace all occurrences of `'周'` with `'\u5468'` in the `parseWeeks` function

